
A:
	Who is that beautiful woman over there? I have never seen something so exquisite.

B:
	Is there anything else?

A:
	Yes.

B:
	Well, then, the matter was as follows--

A:
	I know I just met you, but I love you with all my heart.

B:
	Like me? Did you ever see the other things, the things beyond?

A:
	(Triumphant, to prove how right 
she has been.) You carry it better than you did!

B:
	Of course: that's why he's a good critic. Besides, if you
take people seriously off the stage, why shouldn't you take them
seriously on it, where they're under some sort of decent restraint?
(He

A:
	You killed my cousin? And now I can never see you again? I cannot live any more.

B:
	He went upstairs.

A:
	Yes.

B:
	Your own heart is the only thing that exists for you.

A:
	With you dead, what keeps me alive?

B:
	Well—there is something.

A:
	Yes, I’m of age to-day.  Quite an important day in my
life, isn’t it?  That is why I am giving this party to-night.  Do sit
down.  [_Still arranging flowers_.]

B:
	I cannot sleep out the night. Perhaps if I held my service during the
night under this pine tree....
